Marpenoth 26: I wish that priest had never set foot in our cathedral! I am
	becoming more and more concerned that his words may be true, that I may
	bring disaster on my followers because of my imperfections. Why could
	not have Arla, my mentor, have chosen another, more sutiable priestess?
	I must fight a constant battle with my temper these days, and have
	taken lately to sitting for long hours in sorrow instead of sleeping.
	And worst of all, yesterday when a party of elven hunters took
	refuge from a snowstorm, I actually found myself attracted to one
	of the leaders. I fear my purity is becoming compromised. I must
	cleanse myself before it is too late.

